The '''Anhembi virus''' (AMBV) is a strain of [[Wyeomyia virus]] in the genus [[Bunyavirus]], belonging serologically to the [[Bunyamwera]] serogroup.It is isolated from the rodent, [[Proechimys iheringi]], and a [[mosquito]], [[Phoniomyia pilicauda]], in São Paulo, Brazil. Until 2001 that virus have not reported to cause disease in humans.<ref>{{cite book|last=Mahy|first=Brian W J|title=A dictionary of virology|date=2001|publisher=Academic Press|location=San Diego, Calif. [u.a.]|isbn=0-12-465327-8|pages=17|edition=3.}}</ref>

