| names = [[Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer|WISE]] J014656.66+423410.0,{{r|Kirkpatrick2012}}<br/>[[Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer|WISE]] 0146+4234{{r|Kirkpatrick2012}}
}}
{{Starbox end}}

'''WISE J014656.66+423410.0''' (designation abbreviated to '''WISE 0146+4234''') is a binary [[brown dwarf]] of [[spectral class]]es T9 and Y0<ref name="Dupuy2015"/> located in the constellation [[Andromeda (constellation)|Andromeda]]. It is approximately 60 [[light-year]]s from [[Earth]].<ref name="Leggett2017"/>.

==Discovery==
'''WISE 0146+4234''' was discovered in 2012 by [[J. Davy Kirkpatrick]] et al. from data, collected by [[Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer|Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer (WISE)]] [[Earth-orbit]]ing [[satellite]] — [[National Aeronautics and Space Administration|NASA]] [[infrared|infrared-wavelength]] 40 [[centimeter|cm]] (16 [[inch|in]]) [[space observatory|space telescope]], which mission lasted from December 2009 to February 2011. In 2012 Kirkpatrick et al. published a paper in [[The Astrophysical Journal]], where they presented discovery of seven new found by WISE [[brown dwarf]]s of [[spectral type]] Y, among which also was WISE 0146+4234.{{r|Kirkpatrick2012}}

==Distance==
The distance of WISE 0146+4234 was initially estimated to be 20 [[light-year]]s from earth.{{r|Kirkpatrick2012}} Later measurements of its [[stellar parallax]] showed that it was actually 60 light-years away.<ref name="Leggett2017"/>

